Pre-Game Insights: Gibraltar will look to kick off their UEFA Nations League campaign in great manner when they take on Liechtenstein on Sunday afternoon.
Gibraltar defeated Andorra in a friendly on Wednesday, with Lincoln Red Imps defender Dan Bent scoring the only goal of the match.
Jurgen Henn’s troops are eyeing their third consecutive clean sheet in all competitions.
Liechtenstein struggled offensively in a 1-0 loss to San Marino.
Both Simon Luchinger and Felix Oberwaditzer are pushing for recalls to the starting XI after the duo came off the bench in the opener.
Under 2.5 goals have been netted in five of the previous six meetings between the two sides in all competitions.
